    <h1>
    Financial Literacy</h1></header>

    <h2>Savings and Investments</h2>

    <p>
      Saving means putting aside money for future use. A saving plan is a
      systematic or regular way to reach a financial goal. People save money for
      emergency needs such as a sudden furnace failure. We also save for
      short-term and long-term goals such as going to university or a house.
      Lastly, we save for security and future needs. People have retirement
      funds that can provide for them when they retire.
    </p>

    <p>
      Investing means committing money in order to gain a financial return You
      can invest in stocks, bonds, and Guaranteed Investment Certificates (GIC).
    </p>

